org.lenskit.util.keys

  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    it.unimi.dsi.fastutil.Function<Long,T>, it.unimi.dsi.fastutil.longs.Long2ObjectFunction<T>, it.unimi.dsi.fastutil.longs.Long2ObjectMap<T>, it.unimi.dsi.fastutil.longs.Long2ObjectSortedMap<T>, Serializable, Map<Long,T>, SortedMap<Long,T>

    @Immutable
public class KeyedObjectMap<T>
extends it.unimi.dsi.fastutil.longs.AbstractLong2ObjectSortedMap<T>
implements Serializable

    A mapping that indexes keyed objects by their keys. This structure works on objects that have an associated key, such as recommendation results or ratings (keyed by user or item ID). The key is extracted from an object by means of a KeyExtractor. This allows the objects to be stored directly, without separate storage for keys. This map stores objects in a list sorted by key, and looks them up with binary search. Therefore, the key extractor should generally be fast (e.g. just calling a getter), in order for this class to be performant.
